Title: SS/TDMA Scheduling of Real-Time Periodic Messages  
Author: Ian R. Philp and Jane W. S. Liu 
Address: Urbana, Urbana, IL 61801  
Affiliation: Real-Time Systems Laboratory Department of Computer Science University of Illinois at  
Abstract: This paper presents several efficient heuristic algorithms for scheduling real-time periodic messages in a satellite-switched time-division multiple access (SS/TDMA) system. Previous work in this area considers messages with identical periods and solves the time-slot assignment (TSA) problem which finds conflict-free schedules while minimizing the transmission schedule length and the number of switching modes. We consider the multiple-period TSA (MP-TSA) problem in which real-time periodic messages have different periods and must be scheduled before their deadlines which are equal to their periods. We present simulation results which show the success rates of our algorithms in finding conflict-free schedules. 
